column3: A hasty movement， action， or statement is sudden， and often done in reaction to something that has just happened.
If you lambast someone， you criticize them severely， usually in public.
Someone who is stern is very serious and strict.
Stringent laws， rules， or conditions are very severe or are strictly controlled.

column2: 出去买东西或者去做日常杂事

column3: the quest for the Holy Grail
If you stalk a person or a wild animal， you follow them quietly in order to kill them， catch them， or observe them carefully.
an animal that is being hunted down， esp. with dogs or hawks; prey

column2: 房顶以下房间以上的储物间

column3: When a new leader is inaugurated， they are formally given their new position at an official ceremony.
When someone or something achieves a more important rank or status， you can say that they are elevated to it.
If you opt for something， or opt to do something， you choose it or decide to do it in preference to anything else.

column2: 玩忽职守，没有尽到义务
column3: If someone in a position of responsibility is negligent， they do not do something which they ought to do.
An influx of people or things into a place is their arrival there in large numbers.
An alleged fact has been stated but has not been proved to be true.
